1. **User Story**

As a **BCO Creator**,  
I want to create , review, edit, and consolidate scheme-wise budget estimations.   
so that:

* I can view DDO-wise submission status under each scheme.

* I can generate system-based estimates for DDOs who have not submitted their budget.

* I can accept DDO submissions individually or in bulk for consolidation.

* I can edit estimates submitted by DDOs, if required.

* I can consolidate multiple DDO submissions into a single BCO-level estimate for each Budget Line

* I can enter outcome related information such as SC/ST/Women/Youth ,SDG, MDPI, Youth, Geography, Sector etc for applicable schemes.

* I can view overall ceiling validation and enter extra amount if required at BCO level.

* I can submit consolidated estimates to the BCO Verifier for further review.

2. **Pre-Conditions**

* System configuration exists for **auto-generation of estimates** based on previous year data.

* Budget Estimation cycle is initiated by the Finance Department.

* DDO Approvers may or may not have submitted their budget estimates for the relevant financial year.

* Budget Lines are mapped to Schemes and DDOs under the BCO.

* Scheme master data is available indicating:

  * Various Outcome such as SC/ST/Women/Youth ,SDG, MDPI, Youth, Geography, Sector mapping is applicable

* Ceiling limits are defined by Finance Department at Department.

* Past expenditure, BE, RE, MTE, and actuals data are available through system integrations (AG / IFMIS / HRMS).

3. **Process Flow – BCO Creator**

**Navigation**

* Login → Budget  → Budget estimation

* System displays a **Scheme-wise list of Budget Lines** mapped to the BCO.

* Each Budget Line shows:

  * Scheme Name

  * HoAs

  * Number of DDO submissions received.

  * Consolidation status (Draft / In Progress / Submitted)

**View DDO-wise Submissions**

* On selecting a Scheme → Budget Line:

  * System displays DDO-wise estimates in a tabular view:

    * DDO Code & Name

    * RE (Current Year)

    * BE1, BE2, BE3

    * Breakup entered (Yes/No)

    * Submission status

    * Accepted by BCO (Yes/No)

**Review & Edit DDO Data**

* BCO can open any DDO submission to:

  * View complete budget details and breakup data

  * Edit RE / BE values if required

  * Edit breakup details (item-wise / salary-wise etc.)

  * Add or modify remarks

* All edits are captured in audit trail.

**System-generated Estimates for Non-submitted DDOs**

* For DDOs with status **Not Submitted**, BCO can:

  * Generate system-based estimates using:

    * Previous year BE/RE

    * Salary auto-calculation rules

    * Configured growth logic

* Generated submissions are marked as **System Generated**.

* BCO can review, edit, and accept these estimates.

**Accept & Freeze DDO Submissions**

* BCO can:

  * Accept individual DDO submissions

  * Accept multiple selected DDO submissions

  * Accept all DDO submissions at once

* On acceptance:

  * Submission is included in consolidation

  * Submission becomes read-only for DDO

* BCO can freeze submissions to prevent further DDO edits by accepting system generated submission.

**Consolidation at BCO Level**

* Consolidation includes only BCO-accepted DDO submissions.

* System-generated submissions are included only after BCO acceptance.

* Consolidation includes:

  * Aggregation of RE, BE1, BE2, BE3

  * Consolidated breakup totals

**Planning Fields (Conditional by Scheme)**

* Based on Scheme configuration, system conditionally displays:

  * Outcome mapping such as SC/ST/Women/Youth ,SDG, MDPI, Youth, Geography, Sector mapping is applicable

  * These fields appear only for schemes where planning tagging is applicable.

* Planning fields are entered once per scheme at consolidated level, not per DDO or per budget line.

**Ceiling Validation**

* System validates overall ceiling applicable to the BCO.

* If consolidated BE exceeds ceiling:

  * System flags “Exceeds Ceiling”

  * Justification and supporting document become mandatory

* Ceiling is not checked at individual budget-line level, only at overall consolidated level.

**Save & Submit**

* BCO can:

  * Save consolidated estimates as Draft

  * Submit consolidated estimates to BCO Verifier

* On submission:

  * Status updates to *Submitted*

  * Workflow moves to BCO Verifier

* Budget Manual of Madhya Pradesh (2012), Page 149, Point 12

7. **Acceptance Criteria**

* BCO can generate system-based estimates for DDOs who have not submitted.

* BCO can accept DDO submissions individually or in bulk.

* Only accepted DDO submissions are included in consolidation.

* BCO can freeze DDO submissions, preventing further DDO edits.

* System-generated submissions remain editable until accepted by BCO.

* Each budget line clearly shows DDO-wise submissions and their statuses.

* BCO Creator can open and review each DDO submission individually.

* BCO Creator can edit RE, BE, breakup, salary and remarks for DDO submissions.

* All edits made by BCO Creator are recorded in audit trail.

* System automatically calculates consolidated RE, BE1, BE2, BE3 from all DDO submissions.

* BCO Creator can view DDO-wise totals vs consolidated totals on the same screen.

* Consolidated values are system-derived and consistent with DDO data.

* Planning data is entered once at consolidated level, not per DDO.

* System validates overall BCO-level ceiling on submission.

* If consolidated BE exceeds ceiling:

  * “Exceeds Ceiling” flag is auto-set

  * Justification text becomes mandatory

  * Supporting document upload becomes mandatory

* If ceiling is not exceeded, justification fields remain hidden.

* BCO Creator can save work as Draft without triggering validations.

* On successful submission, request moves to BCO Verifier.

* Submitted records become read-only for BCO Creator.

* BCO can view submission status for all DDOs under a scheme.
